#TECHNICAL INSIGHTS/DISCOVERIES FROM RESEARCH
#   Takeaway - Windows can't use CUDA with current PyTorch builds for the RTX 5070, making Linux the only envioronment for GPU-based YOLO. Linux also can't use internal webcams, meaning only external USB cameras can be used.
#   Source   -  WSL2 documentation, PyTorch CUDA compatability notes, system-level testing

#BLOCK/ISSUES FROM TODAY
#   Issue          - GPU not usable on Windows for YOLO
#   Possible Cause - RTX5070 can't interface with current PyTorch CUDA builds on windows, GPU is only available insude Ubuntu subsystem
#   Solution?      - Continue making code on VS code, but when want to test YOLO with camera footage, run inside of Linux where CUDA is supported

#   Issue          - No camera detected on Ubuntu
#   Possible Cause - Ubuntu can't access internal laptop webcam
#   Solution?      - Use external USB webcam and attach it to Ubuntu

